dataset.description: Customer information dataset capturing essential details such as names, contact information, account status, and country codes, aiding in customer relationship management and outreach efforts.

metadata.description: Unique identifier for each customer in the dataset.
The first name of the customer.
The surname of the customer, used for identification and personalization.
Contact number of the customer; Format is a standard phone number.
Email address of the customer; Used for communication and account-related notifications.
ISO code representing the country of the customer.
Date when the customer account was opened; Format is YYYY-MM-DD.
Flags indicating the status or special conditions of the customer's account; Typically used for categorizing accounts.

dataset.description: Order records detailing transaction amounts, dates, statuses, and categories, providing insights into customer purchasing behavior.

metadata.description: Unique identifier for each order placed by customers.
Unique identifier for the customer who placed the order.
Current status of the order; Indicates whether the order is Finished, Started, or Approved.
The category of the order, indicating the type of service or product being purchased.
Date when the order was placed; Format is YYYY-MM-DD.
Total monetary value of the order; Represents the cost associated with the order.
